AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000117 pmdco:PMD_0000000 "PERSON: Joerg Waitelonis")

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0000001 (portion of matter)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000114 pmdco:PMD_0000001 obo:IAO_0000122)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000117 pmdco:PMD_0000001 "PERSON: Joerg Waitelonis")

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0000005 (materielles Eigentum)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000114 pmdco:PMD_0000005 obo:IAO_0000122)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000117 pmdco:PMD_0000005 "PERSON: Joerg Waitelonis")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment pmdco:PMD_0000005 "A property is a material trait in terms of the kind and magnitude of response to a specific imposed stimulus. Generally, definitions of properties are made independent of material shape and size.
(Callister, W.D., Rethwisch, D.G., Materials Science and Engineering, Wiley, 2014)

Technical materials are complex aggregates. Many properties that are determined for those aggregates are intrinsically associated with the methodologies employed in the measurement process. This is in contrast to typical 'physical' properties, which like e.g. mass that can be determined to high accuracy independently of the measurement process. 
As a consequence, material properties in the ontology are differeciated according to their measurement method, e.g. Brinell hardness and Vickers hardness are different types of indentation hardness rather than different measures/quantification (GDC) of the materials property 'indentation hardness'.
 The 'unit idenifieres' of such properties (e.g. \"HV1\", \"HV10\", \"HBW\") are strictly speaking not units but rather references to the measurement methodology used to determine a numeric value that quantifies the property.

Extensive properties that depend on the object being tested rather than on the portion of matter are (extensive) object- or system-properties."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0000005 "material property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0000005 "materielles Eigentum"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition pmdco:PMD_0000005 "a disposition of a portion of matter that is realized in a compatible process and whose realization is grounded in the portions intensive qualities"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition pmdco:PMD_0000005 "eine Disposition eines Teils der Materie, die in einem kompatiblen Prozess realisiert wird und deren Umsetzung auf den intensiven Eigenschaften der Teile beruht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0000005 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0000005 obo:BFO_0000016)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0000005 ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:BFO_0000054 pmdco:PMD_0000950))
SubClassOf(Annotation(rdfs:comment "Due to the duality of object and portion of matter this axiom can not be an equivalent class axiom."@en) pmdco:PMD_0000005 ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000052 ObjectIntersectionOf(pmdco:PMD_0000001 ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000056 obo:BFO_0000015))))

